<paragraph blockId="5.[192,720,1272,1333]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,470,1272,1298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Taxonomic position of</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco et Rossi, 2017" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[478,720,1272,1299]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus brignolii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; ROSSI" box="[192,491,1306,1333]" firstAuthor="Lourenco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">
Lourenço et Rossi, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[432,491,1306,1332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">2017</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,802,1370,1915]" lastBlockId="5.[830,1440,199,345]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[240,455,1370,1393]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[240,455,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a juvenile, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco &amp; Rossi" box="[192,486,1401,1424]" firstAuthor="Lourenco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço &amp; Rossi (2017)</bibRefCitation>
in the original description, incorrectly declared as a male. It is evident from the sternopectinal area and pectines that it is juvenile female, and it displays typical juvenile morphology and color, as shown in fig. 9 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco &amp; Rossi" firstAuthor="Lourenco" page="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço &amp; Rossi (2017: 6)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition to the above observations, we note that the juvenile 
<typeStatus box="[329,423,1585,1608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[463,588,1585,1608]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[463,588,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and juveniles of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kraepelin, 1896" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
Kraepelin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, that we have studied, match closely in the following key described characters: trichobothrial pattern, pectinal tooth count and lamellar structure, proportions, setation, carination and sculpture of pedipalps, carapace, tergites, sternites, and metasoma, shape of the telson, as well as armature of pedipalp fingers. However, the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[622,749,1800,1823]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[622,749,1800,1823]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" box="[402,492,1830,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis box="[402,492,1830,1853]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is complicated by the listed type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[372,498,1861,1884]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[372,498,1861,1884]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[516,798,1861,1884]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[192,522,1892,1915]" country="Central African Republic" name="Bamingui-Bangoran" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Bamingui-Bangoran Province</collectingRegion>
) which lies outside the known range of distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1896" box="[1174,1263,199,222]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis box="[1174,1263,199,222]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1280,1384,199,222]" name="Tanzania" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
). We therefore regard 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco et Rossi, 2017" authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[1012,1227,230,253]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus brignolii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco et Rossi" firstAuthor="Lourenco" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref17442" refString="LOURENCO W. R. &amp; A. ROSSI. 2017. A new species of Babycurus Karsch, 1886 from dry savannahs in Central African Republic (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Onychium, 13: 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2017">Lourenço et Rossi, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis box="[939,1098,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">nomen dubium</emphasis>
until either the true distribution of both species is revised, or an adult topotype specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lourenco et Rossi" authorityYear="2017" box="[859,982,322,345]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis box="[859,982,322,345]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B. brignolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
